    {
      "key": "75fc097e-7279-448f-971f-fc0a8dc6ea7d",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-video-camera\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Video:** Show the video “The Internet: Packets, Routing, and Reliability”",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "To encourage active engagement and reflection, use one or more of the strategies discussed in the [**Guide to Curriculum Videos**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Y-kGl_pc2afuSBKhKkdulu53X50mc7T-RQZA4vGLpY4/edit?usp=sharing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "75fc097e-7279-448f-971f-fc0a8dc6ea7d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "371bd62b-6740-488b-8dfc-6c2ef104adf4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c22aae23-64fd-4b81-93c5-561b4ac0d6d5",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c22aae23-64fd-4b81-93c5-561b4ac0d6d5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "371bd62b-6740-488b-8dfc-6c2ef104adf4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "987f8ce2-06dd-493e-8e97-609732522d06",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n- *What vulnerabilities allowed the hacker to breach Acme Corporation’s network?*\n- *What could Acme have done to prevent the attack?*\n- *What impact did the attack have on Acme, and how do you think it could impact their customers?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students recognize that multiple security failures—including weak passwords, social engineering, and multi-factor authentication (MFA) fatigue—enabled the hacker to breach Acme Corporation’s network. Guide students to identify how better security practices, such as stronger password policies, improved multi-factor authentication, and offline backups, could have prevented the attack. Encourage students to consider the broader consequences, including financial loss, reputational damage, and compromised customer data.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "987f8ce2-06dd-493e-8e97-609732522d06",
        "lesson_activity.key": "371bd62b-6740-488b-8dfc-6c2ef104adf4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4513c6b6-9ad5-40d8-ab3d-f0e555845b79",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Place students in pairs or small groups of three. Make sure students have their Unit Guide out and opened to Lesson 9.",
        "name": "Network Defense",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Identify, Defend, Reflect! activity is an interactive game in which students will use a clickable slideshow that will navigate them through various network vulnerabilities. The goals of the activity are to:\n- Discover common network vulnerabilities\n- Investigate key details of those vulnerabilities\n- Identify appropriate defenses in network vulnerability scenarios\n\nThe game is covers four common network vulnerabilities. Each should take about 7 minutes to complete. We recommend modeling the first vulnerability to demonstrate how to interact with the slideshow."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4513c6b6-9ad5-40d8-ab3d-f0e555845b79",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e0498937-2059-4bc3-9394-b15848626c25"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "96a1dac7-d46f-4945-aae7-4bab141983d9",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "96a1dac7-d46f-4945-aae7-4bab141983d9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e0498937-2059-4bc3-9394-b15848626c25"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "39261de1-b1bc-46e6-8d94-657ce9f29ec4",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Today, you'll step into the role of a cybersecurity analyst, investigating real-world security threats and deciding how to defend against them. Follow the instructions in the interactive slide deck, record your observations in your Unit Guide, and think critically about how to protect networks from cyber attacks",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "39261de1-b1bc-46e6-8d94-657ce9f29ec4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e0498937-2059-4bc3-9394-b15848626c25"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "79ac9e9d-a535-4a9e-8a4f-b0ea5b9a4b13",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:**  Direct students to Lesson 9, Level 1. Lead the class through a demonstration of the first “round” of the interactive slide show. Walk them through one scenario and model how to navigate through the slides and record notes in the unit guide. Then, release students to work with their partners to complete the remaining scenarios. ",
        "progression_name": "Identify, Defend, Reflect!"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "79ac9e9d-a535-4a9e-8a4f-b0ea5b9a4b13",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e0498937-2059-4bc3-9394-b15848626c25"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "25e5edd3-016a-44b5-ac58-74c401ae8d71",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** As students work through the slides, check that students are following the instructions and recording observations. Listen for discussions between partners—are they just clicking through, or are they analyzing the scenarios. When students are selecting defenses, ask probing questions about what made them choose certain options.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *If you were a cybersecurity analyst for Cybershield Inc., which mitigation strategy would you prioritize implementing first, and why?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students think critically about the mitigation strategies they encountered in the interactive slideshow. They discuss the importance of a variety of mitigation strategies and the consequences of not having those strategies in place.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 9, Level 2 to complete the Check for Understanding.",
        "progression_name": "Check for Understanding"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "25e5edd3-016a-44b5-ac58-74c401ae8d71",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e0498937-2059-4bc3-9394-b15848626c25"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "45d6dcdb-7d64-45b1-9a99-4455e20a851a",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "45d6dcdb-7d64-45b1-9a99-4455e20a851a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e0498937-2059-4bc3-9394-b15848626c25"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "69d94bbf-ac38-40a0-8e3b-95daf76ecc6f",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Give students a quick minute to jot down their thoughts on the Question of the Day. Encourage students to include at least one specific example from any of today’s activities.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Question of the Day effectively assesses the lesson objectives if students provide responses that explain:\n- common network security vulnerabilities.\n- solutions to mitigate security risks."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "69d94bbf-ac38-40a0-8e3b-95daf76ecc6f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "05c77d84-e74e-49e8-80b7-320b53047be0"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d7440d94-07fe-416c-9aa9-5f6c1ff942dd",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d7440d94-07fe-416c-9aa9-5f6c1ff942dd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "05c77d84-e74e-49e8-80b7-320b53047be0"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8640aa0a-b3b3-41b4-9b98-50159f6564e7",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Label the four corners of the room: Phishing, Weak Passwords, Social Engineering, Default Credentials. Instruct students to go to the corner that relates to the one vulnerability they mentioned in their question of the day answer. Have students share their answers and compare mitigation strategies. If time allows, have one person from each group share one takeaway from their discussion with the class.\n"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8640aa0a-b3b3-41b4-9b98-50159f6564e7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "05c77d84-e74e-49e8-80b7-320b53047be0"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "12f3e877-afb6-44d1-8098-7bd88b9565d5",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-video-camera\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Video:**  Show the video “AI-Based, Real-Time Threat Detection” to students. \n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *How does detecting threats in real time improve network security compared to delayed detection? What challenges might companies face when adopting AI-driven security tools like Morpheus? How could these challenges be addressed?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:**This discussion prepares students to think critically about the role of AI in modern cybersecurity and its real-world applications. Students analyze how real-time threat detection improves network security, contrasting AI-driven tools with traditional methods that often detect threats too late. Encourage students to consider how faster detection helps prevent breaches and limits damage. Guide them to recognize the challenges organizations face when implementing AI security tools, such as cost, training, or false positives, and how these barriers can be addressed.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Ensure students are making connections between AI’s strengths and challenges. Ask questions like,*“What happens if AI misidentifies a threat?”*or*“Why might some organizations be hesitant to rely on AI security tools?”*"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "12f3e877-afb6-44d1-8098-7bd88b9565d5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "94df1681-a42a-4558-ade3-90da1ca709b6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fdd90f9c-8199-40d2-a99d-add2503088dd",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fdd90f9c-8199-40d2-a99d-add2503088dd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "94df1681-a42a-4558-ade3-90da1ca709b6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7b0279f6-188a-400b-830f-91fe3ca8bc35",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Explain to students that today, they are diving into one of the most cutting-edge topics in cybersecurity—how AI is revolutionizing network security. Every second, massive amounts of data are moving through networks, and cyber threats are evolving just as quickly. Traditional security methods struggle to keep up, but AI is changing the game by detecting threats in real time before they cause damage. As they explore AI-driven security tools today, encourage students to think critically about whether AI is the ultimate solution, or does it have its own risks and challenges.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Introduce the Question of the Day."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7b0279f6-188a-400b-830f-91fe3ca8bc35",
        "lesson_activity.key": "94df1681-a42a-4558-ade3-90da1ca709b6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bd132e53-2629-460b-aa96-8c08e567e244",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Put students into groups of two.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:**  Give each pair of students a copy of the Threat Detected! Cards and the AI Threat Detection Notetaker activity guide.",
        "name": "AI Threat Detection"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bd132e53-2629-460b-aa96-8c08e567e244",
        "lesson_activity.key": "41e63e92-fd5f-412a-a862-3ab61104bb12"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ba10deb5-4f6e-4435-a596-d54b1308c28d",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Today, you will act as security analysts, using an AI threat detection system to investigate and respond to security threats. Your goal is to evaluate how AI-based security tools work compared to traditional detection methods. Work with your partner to complete this activity. You will receive one set of AI Threat Detection Cards and you will each have your own Threat Detection Notetaker to fill out individually.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ba10deb5-4f6e-4435-a596-d54b1308c28d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "41e63e92-fd5f-412a-a862-3ab61104bb12"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "975bfcf2-fe53-4c8d-9380-a221fd806d73",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Explain that students will act as security analysts interacting with an AI threat detection system to analyze and respond to network vulnerabilities. Review the steps for drawing a Threat Detected card, discussing the scenario with the AI Chatbot, recording the results of the discussion on the Activity Guide, and then drawing a new card to repeat the process.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:**  Direct students to Lesson 10, Level 1 to interact with the threat detection chatbot and complete their activity guide. ",
        "progression_name": "Threat Detection Chatbot"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "975bfcf2-fe53-4c8d-9380-a221fd806d73",
        "lesson_activity.key": "41e63e92-fd5f-412a-a862-3ab61104bb12"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ed46a64a-1524-4d9e-8a7a-54a492db96c0",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Give students at least 20 minutes to complete as many threat cards as possible in that time. Then, direct student to move on to Level 2 to complete a check for understanding. \n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:**  Circulate and listen for students who assume AI is always accurate. If students trust the AI’s responses without question, ask: ‘Could AI ever misidentify a threat? How would that impact security?’ Ensure students also consider limitations like false positives, AI bias, and the need for human oversight.",
        "progression_name": "Check for Understanding",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, display anonymous student responses for the check for understanding on Level 2 and go over misconceptions or ask students what similarities and differences they notice about the responses."
          },
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "Level 2 can be used to formatively assess the learning objectives."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ed46a64a-1524-4d9e-8a7a-54a492db96c0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "41e63e92-fd5f-412a-a862-3ab61104bb12"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1f287d75-2bc8-4d58-a3c4-41f5bce0f1aa",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1f287d75-2bc8-4d58-a3c4-41f5bce0f1aa",
        "lesson_activity.key": "41e63e92-fd5f-412a-a862-3ab61104bb12"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9d4ee7bc-9c3f-4dd8-b346-aade0343c76a",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Put students into groups of four. \n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Instruct students to choose one scenario from their activity and discuss with their group how AI detected the threat and how that compared to traditional methods.**\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:**  Encourage students to move beyond ‘AI is faster’ as their key argument. Ask: ‘Does AI replace human analysts completely? What tasks might still require human decision-making?’ Look for responses that mention AI’s adaptability, scalability, and data processing power while recognizing that human oversight is still necessary.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:**  Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n- *What patterns did you notice in AI’s responses to each threat?*\n- *How did AI improve security compared to traditional methods?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:**  Students analyze patterns in AI’s responses to security threats and evaluate its strengths and weaknesses. Encourage them to consider what AI does well (speed, data analysis, automation) and where it struggles (bias, detecting new types of threats, false positives). Guide them to recognize that AI is a tool, not a replacement for human decision-making in cybersecurity.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Explain to students that the next slides will have a statement about AI and cybersecurity. Students will hold a thumbs up for True, thumbs down for False, or thumbs sideways for unsure. Once students have held up their answer, you will reveal the correct answer and explain why.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Read the slide and ask students to choose whether it’s true or false. Once students have indicated their answer, move onto the next slide to reveal and discuss.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Explain why the statement is false: AI is powerful, but it’s not perfect—some scams still slip through. Hackers continuously adapt their methods, and AI can sometimes generate false positives or miss subtle attacks. Human judgement should be the first line of defense. Remind students that if they are unsure whether something is a scam, take a step back and cross-check with a trusted source, like speaking to the person who sent the message in person.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Read the slide and ask students to choose whether it’s true or false. Once students have indicated their answer, move onto the next slide to reveal and discuss.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Explain why the statement is false: Social engineering works because it looks convincing—attackers impersonate real people, use familiar logos, and create a sense of urgency. Remind students to always examine the sender details, such as looking to see if the email address matches the school or company’s domain. Other ways you can tell are any red flags, like urgent requests, odd grammar, or messages that ask for personal information.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Read the slide and ask students to choose whether it’s true or false. Once students have indicated their answer, move onto the next slide to reveal and discuss.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Explain why the statement is false: Even responding to a scam email can be dangerous—attackers confirm active accounts based on responses and might target students again. Remind students that when in doubt, use this approach: ‘STOP-THINK-VERIFY’ before interacting with any suspicious message. Never respond to a message with any personal information before verifying that it is actually the person they say they are. The best way to do this is to ask the person in real life."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9d4ee7bc-9c3f-4dd8-b346-aade0343c76a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "41e63e92-fd5f-412a-a862-3ab61104bb12"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d7c6cdbf-6775-4a26-9a4d-daa1feb19b96",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d7c6cdbf-6775-4a26-9a4d-daa1feb19b96",
        "lesson_activity.key": "41e63e92-fd5f-412a-a862-3ab61104bb12"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "df7201f3-79da-4c95-8af0-92658fc5a6cd",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Review the learning objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Place students in pairs or small groups of three.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to briefly share their thoughts about what makes AI effective at enhancing network security and how it compares to traditional methods before individually writing their own response to the Question of the Day in their Unit Guide.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Encourage students to go beyond basic thoughts such as “it’s faster” by making connections to today’s activities."
          },
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Question of the Day effectively assesses the lesson objectives if students provide responses that explain:\n- the role of AI in real-time threat detection.\n- An example of AI-based solutions to network security challenges."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "df7201f3-79da-4c95-8af0-92658fc5a6cd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "47cc1f8f-9d15-47f6-84d2-72fb93f8517d"
      }
    },
